The Alex Jones Show
Thurssday, 02 September 2010


[sebaygo1]



Scheduled Guests
................


Alex welcomes back to the show James Delingpole, the British columnist and novelist who writes for The Times, The Daily Telegraph, and as a television critic for The Spectator. Delingpole is a critic of the man-made climate change theory and contends proponents of the theory exaggerate or otherwise manipulate data to bolster the case for anthropogenic climate change. Delingpole is the author of How to be Right: The Essential Guide to Making Lefty Liberals History.

NOTE :: In the final seconds of hour 3, Alex announced that he was going to go into a 4th hour, OverDrive segment.  Actual duration approx. 27 mins.
